CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F178A1782361075
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/2
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CFriday:FSome early sunshine across
OL,6,FArgyll, but generally a cloudy day
OL,7,Fwith outbreaks of occasionally heavy,
OL,8,Fperhaps thundery rain, spreading
OL,9,Fnorth. Rain turning lighter and
OL,10,Fpatchier through afternoon. Cooler
OL,11,Fthan recently.
OL,12,
OL,13,COutlook for Saturday to Monday:FSome
OL,14,Fmorning sunny spells Saturday but
OL,15,Foccasionally heavy, perhaps thundery,
OL,16,Frain spreading east in afternoon.
OL,17,FSunday and Monday see sunny spells and
OL,18,Fshowers, with a fresh southwesterly
OL,19,Fbreeze. Much cooler.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
